WinRS (Windows Remote Shell) is a command-line tool built into Windows that enables systems administrators to securely execute commands, scripts, or programs on remote Windows computers. It functions as the command-line client for Windows Remote Management (WinRM) Microsoft's implementation of the WS-Management (Web Services for Management) protocol.

While WMI (Windows Management Instrumentation) acts as the data provider—supplying information about system resources—WinRS acts as the transport mechanism to interact with that data remotely,
